briefdescription.para: Constructs a newly allocated Command object.
Constructs a newly allocated TemplCommand object for a command with a name and an execution method.

detaileddescription.para: This constructor set the command input and output type to Tango::DEV_VOID. The input and output parameter description are set to the default String "Uninitialised". The command display level is set to OPERATOR.

parameterdescription.para: Pointer to the command execution method

briefdescription.para: Choose the correct TANGO data type constant according to data type.

detaileddescription.para: The TANGO constant is determined using the type_info object passed as first argument of the method. This data is compared to each defined Tango type.

parameterdescription.para: A reference where Tango data type constant must be stored
If the type is not a Tango data type Click here to read DevFailed exception specification

briefdescription.para: Invoke the command execution method given at object creation time.

detaileddescription.para: This method is automatically called by the TANGO core classes when the associated command is requested by a client.

parameterdescription.para: The device on which the command must be executed
The incoming data still packed in a CORBA Any object. For command created with this TemplCommand class, this Any object does not contain usefull data

simplesect.para: The CORBA Any object returned to the client. For command created with this TemplCommand class, this any object does not contain data.

parameterdescription.para: If the execution method failed Click here to read DevFailed exception specification

briefdescription.para: Invoke the command allowed method given at object creation time.

detaileddescription.para: This method is automtically called by the TANGO core classes when the associated command is requested by a client to check if the command is allowed in the actual device state. If the user give a command allowed method at object creation time, this method will be invoked.

parameterdescription.para: The device on which the command must be executed
The incoming data still packed in a CORBA Any object. For command created with this TemplCommand class, this Any object does not contain data

simplesect.para: A boolean set to true is the command is allowed. Otherwise, the return value is false. This return value is always set to true if the user does not supply a method to be excuted. If a method has been supplied, the return value is the value returned by the user supplied mehod.

briefdescription.para: The command allowed method object reference.

memberdef.argsstring: (const char *, const char *, const char *, DispLevel)
memberdef.name: TemplCommand

briefdescription.para: This class is a class representing a command in the template command model without input or output parameter.
